   <Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Product Number*

A key that uniquely identifies the product.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Plant*

Key uniquely identifying a plant.
In Logistics a plant is an organizational unit for dividing an enterprise according to production, procurement, maintenance, and products planning.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">MRP Type

Key that determines whether and how the product is planned. This field becomes mandatory if MRP data should be migrated.
Depending on the MRP type other fields are becomming mandatory eg if you choose 'VB' for reorder-point planning you also have to specify the Reorder Point, MRP controller, Lot Sizing Procedure ...

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">MRP Controller

Specifies the number of the MRP controller or group of MRP controllers responsible for product planning for the product.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Availability Check

Every product that is to take part in the availability check must be assigned to a checking group.
Using the checking group you can define:
- Whether the products to be checked are locked during the availability check
- Whether the normal ATP quantity or the cumulated ATP quantity is used.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Plant-Specific Product Status

The product status determines how a product is handled in different applications and in business operations (for example, purchasing, products planning, usage in bills of material ..). If a product has a product status, the system will issue either a warning or an error message (depending on which status you have chosen) if the product is used.
Note: The plant-specific product status restricts the usability of the product for this specific plant.
Please see further information in the migration object documentation under Mapping instructions.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Valid From Date for Status

Date from which the plant-specific product status is valid.

Type: Date</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Profit Center

An organizational unit in Accounting that reflects a management-oriented structure of the organization for the purpose of internal control.
Operating results for a profit center can be analyzed using either the cost of sales approach or the period accounting approach.
By analyzing the fixed capital as well, you can expand your profit center for use as an investment center.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Unit of Issue (ISO Format)

Enter a value in this field only if you want to use a unit of measure differing from the base unit of measure.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Batch Management Req. Indicator

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Specifies whether the product is managed in batches ('X') or not (<blank>) in the specified plant.
Please consider the settings in configuration defined for 'Specify Batch Management Default by Plant'.
Note: to assign the batch class to your product please use migration object 'Material classification'.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Serial Number Profile

Note: Serial number management is not possible with backflushing.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Negative Stocks Allowed in Plant

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Stock Determination Group

The stock determination group combined with the stock determination rule at plant level create a key for the stock determination strategy.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Loading Group

A grouping of products that share the same loading requirements.
The system uses the loading group as well as the ' Shipping conditions' and 'Delivering plant' to automatically determine the shipping point for the item in sales and transfer documents (for example Sales Order, outbound delivery).

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Co-Product

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.
Indicator you can use to specify that the product can also be used as a co-product.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Batch Entry in Production

This indicator refers to the components of an order, not to the finished product to be manufactured. You have the following options:
•The batches can be determined when the goods issue is posted.
•The batches must be entered in the order before it is released.
•The batches must be entered in the order before the goods issue is posted, but not necessarily before the order is released.
•The batches are determined automatically when the order is released.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Indicator: Critical Part

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Documentation Required Indicator

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inspection Interval in Days

Specifies the interval between different quality inspections.

Type: Number
Length: 5</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Quality Management Control Key

This key determines which conditions are valid for quality management in procurement.
Note: This field must only be filled if there will be a related Quality Info record existing in the system. If the fields are filled and the QIR is missing, the business process will run into an error.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Certificate Type

Defines the content of a quality certificate.


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Country/Region of Origin

Key of the country/region in which the product has been produced.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Region of Origin

You can enter a region of the country/region from which the goods originate.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Taxes in International Trade

Control code for consumption taxes in foreign trade.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Material CFOP Category

Use for BRAZIL only !
The CFOP category is used to determine the proper CFOP.


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Purchasing Group

Internally, the purchasing group is responsible for the procurement of a product or a class of products.
Externally, it is the medium through which contacts with the supplier are maintained.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Post to Inspection Stock

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Source List Required

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Automatic Purchase Oder Allowed

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Tax Indicator

Please enter the Tax indicator for product (Purchasing) for the related country/region of your plant.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">ABC Indicator

Indicator that classifies a product as an A, B, or C part according to its consumption value. This classification process is known as the ABC analysis.
The three indicators have the following meanings:
•A - important part, high consumption value
•B - less important part, medium consumption value
•C - relatively unimportant part, low consumption value

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">MRP Group

The MRP group contains all the products from the point of view of MRP for assigning special control parameters for the total planning run. These control parameters include, for example, the strategy group, the consumption mode, and the planning horizon.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Strategy Group

The strategy group groups all the planning strategies that can be used for a particular product. The planning strategy represents the procedure used for planning a product and is (technically speaking) controlled by the MRP types.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Reorder Point

For MRP Type 'VB' (Reorder-Point-Planning) you have to specify the reorder point for reorder planning. In this case this field becomes mandatory. If the stock falls below this quantity, the system flags the product for requirements planning.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planning Time Fence

The planning fence time becomes required if you are working with MRP type which includes a firming type. This is for example the case for MRP type P1-P4 (Forecast Consumption, Auto/Manual Firming).
The planning time fence specifies a period within which no automatic changes are to be made to the master plan.
The planning time fence is maintained in workdays.


Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planning Cycle

Key that determines the day on which the product is planned and ordered.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Consumption Mode

The consumption mode controls the direction on the time axis in which the system consumes requirements.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Consumption Period: Backward

Determines the consumption period (in workdays) for backward consumption.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Consumption Period: Forward

Determines the consumption period (in workdays) for forward consumption.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Mixed MRP Indicator

Defines the indicator for planning assemblies.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planning Product

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planning Plant

Planning plant which specifically identifies the plant from which the planned independent requirements of the reference product comes from.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Plng. Conv. Factor

Factor that the system uses to convert the quantity of the current product, measured in the base unit of measure, to the base unit quantity of the planning product.

Example:

Base unit of measure for Planning product: to
Base unit of measure for Current product: kg

--> Conversion factor = 0.001 because 1 kg = 0.001 to


Type: Text
Length: 10</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Lot Sizing Procedure

Key that determines which lot-sizing procedure the system uses within products planning to calculate the quantity to be procured or produced.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Minimum Lot Size

Minimum procurement quantity.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Maximum Lot Size

Quantity that is not allowed to be exceeded during procurement.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Fixed Lot Size

Please enter a value if you are working with Lot Sizing Procedure 'Fixed order quantity'. The fixed lot size is then a required field.
Note: In this case entries in fields: Minimum Lot Size, Maximum Lot Size and Rounding value will be reset.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Storage Cost Indicator

Indicator that specifies the storage costs percentage the system uses when calculating the lot size to determine storage costs.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Lot Size Independant Cost

Costs that are incurred, irrespective of lot size, for each purchase order or production order over and above the purchase order price or production costs.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Currency for Lot Size Ind. Cost

You must specify the currency for the Lot Size Independent Cost (currency of the company code belonging to the plant).

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Assembly Scrap (%)

Percentage scrap that occurs during production of the product if the product is an assembly.
The assembly scrap is used in products planning to calculate the lot size of the assembly. The system increases the quantity to be produced by the scrap quantity calculated.

Type: Number
Length: 5
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Maximum Stock Level

Quantity of the product in this plant that may not be exceeded.
In products planning, the maximum stock level is used only if you have chosen Replenish to maximum stock level as the lot-sizing procedure; that is, you have entered HB as the lot size key.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Rounding Value

Value to a multiple of which the system rounds up the procurement quantity.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Takt Time

If a requirement quantity (for example, for capacity reasons) cannot be procured in a single lot, you have to schedule several receipts. In conjunction with the overlap indicator in the lot size, you can use the takt time to specify that these receipts are offset, that is, that they are delayed by the takt time.
You enter the takt time in workdays.


Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Rounding Profile

Key that the system uses to adjust the order proposal quantity to deliverable units.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Safety Stock

Specifies the quantity whose purpose is to satisfy unexpectedly high demand in the coverage period.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Minimum Safety Stock

The quantity that defines the lower limit for safety stock.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Safety Time (in Workdays)

In this field, you define the number of workdays for the safety time/actual range of coverage. If you define a safety time, the requirements in MRP are brought forward on the time axis by the number of workdays you define here.

Type: Number
Length: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Service Level Warehouse

Percentage specifying what proportion of the requirement is to be covered by the warehouse stock.

Type: Number
Length: 3
Decimal: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Coverage Profile

The range of coverage profile contains the parameters for calculating the dynamic safety stock. This is a statistical calculation on the basis of average daily requirements.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Safety Time Indicator

You use this indicator to switch on the safety time actual range of coverage for a product in MRP.
If you define a safety time, the requirements in MRP are brought forward on the time axis by the number of workdays you define here. The actual range of coverage corresponds to the number of days, by which the requirements are brought forward. Using this indicator you can activate the safety time and you can set whether all requirements or only independent requirements (sales order, planned independent requirements, and so on) are to be brought forward.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Safety Time Period Profile

The period profile for the safety time / actual range of coverage contains the periods (stating to/from date) with the safety time/actual range of coverage that is valid for each period.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">MRP Relevancy for Dependent Requirements

MRP relevancy (Materials Requirements Planning) for dependent requirements:
This indicator controls whether dependent requirements are relevant to MRP or not. Dependent requirements include dependent reservations and stock transfer requirements. You only use this indicator in connection with planning strategies for make-to-stock production, assembly planning.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Safety Stock Method

The MRP Safety Stock Method provides different options to introduce a safety buffer.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Individual / Collective Requirements

Dependent requirements indicator for individual and coll. requirements.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Component Scrap in Percent

Component scrap is used in product requirements planning (MRP) to determine the quantities of components required. When exploding the bill of material (BOM), the system increases the required quantities of the components by the calculated scrap quantity.

Type: Number
Length: 5
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Requirements Group

Defines whether the system groups together dependent requirements for the product on a daily basis when analyzing requirements planning.
Defines whether additional individual/dependent requirements are written for components whose assembly is set such that total dependent requirements are created.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Discontinuation Ind.

Identifies the product as a part to be discontinued and includes it in the discontinued parts procedure in products planning.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Effective-Out Date

Date from which the stocks of the product are to be used up. As soon as no more stock exists for this product, it is to be replaced by the follow-up product.

Type: Date</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Follow-Up Product

Number of the product that the system uses in products planning to replace the product to be discontinued once its warehouse stock is depleted.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Indicator: Repetitive Manufa. Allow

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty. The repetitive manufacturing profile also determines;
•how the system deals with activities when backflushing
•which movement type is used to post goods receipts and goods issues
•how planned order and run schedule quantities are reduced in the backflush transaction
•how BOM corrections are made - if errors should occur when posting quantities to be backflushed

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Repetitive Manufacturing Profile

Controls, via order type, whether you are working with make-to-order repetitive manufacturing, based on sales orders, or with make-to-stock repetitive manufacturing, based on no specific orders.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Procurement Type

Indicator that defines how the product is procured. The following procurements types are possible:
• E = The product is produced in-house.
• F = The product is procured externally.
• X = The product can be both produced in-house and procured externally.


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Special Procurement Type

The special procurement type is used to precisely define how in-house production and external procurement is to be carried out. Example: Special Procurement for External Procurement can be Consignment, Subcontracting ...

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Issue Storage Location

Default storage location for produced inhouse.
In the case of a product produced in-house, this is the key of the storage location that is copied to the planned order, production order, or run schedule quantity. If the product is a component, it is the issuing storage location to which a backflush is posted.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Replenishment Lead Time

The total replenishment lead time is the time needed before the product is completely available again, that is, after all BOM levels have been procured or produced. It is not calculated by the system, but defined in this field as the total of the in-house production time(s) and/or the planned delivery time(s) of the longest production path.
This time is necessary if, for products produced in-house, the replenishment lead time is to be taken into consideration in the availability check.


Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Cross-Project

Determines if the system takes all stock and MRP-relevant units (inward/outward movement) in the project stock segments for all documents without account assignment into consideration.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Default Storage Loc. for Ext. Procuremet

Default storage location for external procurement.
Storage location that is proposed in the purchase requisition in products planning for subsequent storage of the product. In the case of a product procured externally, this storage location is proposed in the planned order in products planning.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planning Calendar

Three character number (numeric or using letters) that specifically identifies a PPS-planning calendar.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">In-House Production Time

Specifies the time in workdays needed to produce the product in-house.
In-house production time is independent of the order quantity.


Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planned Delivery Time

Number of calendar days needed to obtain the product or service if it is procured externally.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Goods Receipt Processing Time

Number of workdays required after receiving the product for inspection and placement into storage.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Backflush

Determines whether the backflush indicator is set in the production order. Here, a 3-level hierarchy logic is applied:
1. In the routing, the backflush indicator is set in the component assignment.
2. In the product master record, the backflush indicator is set to "Always Backflush".
3. In the product master record, the backflush indicator is set to "Work Center Decides", and the indicator is set in the work center.

Each product component is assigned to an operation in the production order. If a product component is backflushed, the system posts the withdrawal only upon confirmation of the operation. The withdrawal is then posted automatically.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Default Supply Area

The supply area is used as an interim storage area on the shop floor which is used to provide products directly at the production line.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">JIT Delivery Sched.

Determines whether it is possible to generate JIT delivery schedules in addition to forecast schedules for a product specified in a purchase scheduling agreement.
If you set this indicator, it will be copied into the additional data for the item when a scheduling agreement is created.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Indicator: Bulk Material

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.
This indicator defines a BOM item as a bulk product, which is available directly at the work center (for example, washers or grease).

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Scheduling Margin Key

Key that the system uses to determine the floats required for scheduling an order. You define the following floats with the scheduling margin key:
• opening period
• float after production (only in the case of in-house production)
• float before production (only in the case of in-house production)
• release period (only in the case of production order management)


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Period Type

Indicator specifying the periods in which the product's consumption values and forecast values are managed.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Fiscal Year Variant

The fiscal year variant is used to define the fiscal year.
You can define the following using a fiscal year variant:
•How many posting periods are in a fiscal year
•How many special periods you require
•How the system determines the posting periods when posting.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Splitting Indicator

Indicator that defines how the system splits forecast requirements into smaller time intervals where the MRP type is forecast-based planning and the period indicator is not "day".

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Reference Plant for Consumption

Plant of the reference product on whose consumption data the product forecast is based.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Reference Product for Consumption

The system uses the consumption data of this product for the forecast.


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Use Referenced Consumption Data Until

Date until which the consumption data of the reference product is used for the product forecast.

Type: Date</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Multiplier for Reference Product

Determines how much of the consumption quantity of the reference product should be used for the product forecast.

Type: Number
Length: 4
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Ind. Reset Forecast Model Auto

Causes that system to reset the forecast model automatically if the tracking limit is exceeded. Furthermore, the system carries out a new model selection during the next forecast.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Ind. Correction Factors

You set this indicator if you want the correction factors to be used in the calculation of the forecast values.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Base Quantity

Quantity to which the in-house production time and the processing time of the product relate.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Overdelivery Tolerance Limit

Percentage rate by which the quantity that is posted to goods receipt may exceed the production order quantity.

Type: Number
Length: 3
Decimal: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Underdelivery Tolerance Limit

Percentage rate that specifies the percent below which the quantity posted for a goods receipt may drop below the production order quantity.

Type: Number
Length: 3
Decimal: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Ind. Unlimited Overdelivery Allowed

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Production Unit (ISO Format)

Enter a value in this field only if you want to use a unit of measure differing from the base unit of measure.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Production Supervisor

Group responsible for controlling the production of a product.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Production Scheduling Profile

Profile that you can use to
•specify that certain business transactions are carried out in parallel in a production order / process order (you can, for example, create and release an order at the same time, or release an order and print the shop papers)
•trigger an automatic goods receipt
•specify an overall profile for capacity leveling

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Setup and Teardown Time

Specifies the number of workdays needed to set up and tear down the various work centers where the product is processed. This value is the total of the setup and teardown times.
The setup and teardown time is independent of the order quantity.

Type: Number
Length: 5
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Interoperation Time

Specifies the number of workdays required for the transition of a produced product between work centers or work center groups.

Type: Number
Length: 5
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Processing Time

Specifies the time in workdays needed to process the product in the operations at the different work centers.
The processing time depends on the order quantity.


Type: Number
Length: 5
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Cycle Counting Indicator

Indicates that the given product is subject to the cycle counting method of inventory.

The indicator also defines at which time intervals a physical inventory is to be carried out for the product.


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Cycle Counting Indicator Fixed

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Set this indicator if the product is always to remain in the specified cycle counting category.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Do Not Cost

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Controls whether a cost estimate or a procurement alternative can be created for a product.
<empty> => Cost
X => Do Not Cost

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Variance Key

Key that controls variance calculation.
Variances can only be calculated for the orders for which a variance key has been entered. This key is defaulted through the costing view in the product master record.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Costing Lot Size

Lot size of the costed object (such as a product or sales order) used in the product cost estimate.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Maximum Storage Period

The longest amount of time allowed for storing the product.

Type: Number
Length: 5</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Unit for Maximum Storage Period

Unit in which the maximum storage period of the product is measured.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Shipping Setup Time

The time needed in shipping to set up the work centers where the product is processed. It is independent of quantity. Shipping setup time is used for capacity planning in shipping.

Type: Number
Length: 5
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Shipping Processing Time

Time that is needed in shipping to process a specific quantity of a product. It refers to the base quantity for capacity planning in shipping.

Type: Number
Length: 5
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Base Quantity for Capacity Planning

Quantity to which the shipping processing time refers. It is measured in the base unit of measure.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Indicator: Storage

You can use this indicator to set the storage view on plant level active. For further information please refer to the migration object documentation.
This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Indicator: Work Scheduling

You can use this indicator to set the work scheduling view on plant level active. For further information please refer to the migration object documentation.
This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Indicator: Purchasing

You can use this indicator to set the purchasing view on plant level active. For further information please refer to the migration object documentation.
This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Indicator: Quality

You can use this indicator to set the quality view on plant level active. For further information please refer to the migration object documentation.
This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Indicator: Sales

You can use this indicator to set the sales view on plant level active. For further information please refer to the migration object documentation.
This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>

   <Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Product Number*

A key that uniquely identifies the product.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Plant*

Key uniquely identifying a plant.
In Logistics a plant is an organizational unit for dividing an enterprise according to production, procurement, maintenance, and products planning.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Forecast Model

Indicator that defines on which forecast model the system bases its calculation of future requirements of the product.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Hist. Periods

The number of historical values the system uses for the forecast.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Forecast Periods

Number of period splits for which a forecast should be created.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Periods Per Season

Number of periods that belong to a season.You only specify a number if the forecast model is a seasonal model or if you want the system to carry out a seasonal test.


Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Initialization Periods

Number of historical values that you want to be used for initialization.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Fixed Periods

Number of periods for which the system will not recalculate the forecast values in the next forecast. The fixed periods start with the initial forecast period.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Initialization

Indicator which specifies that the system should initialize a forecast model. The system also calculates the parameters that are needed for the model (such as basic value, trend value, and seasonal indices).

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Tracking Limit

Value that specifies the amount by which the forecast value may deviate from the actual value.

Type: Number
Length: 5
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Model Selection

Indicator used in forecast model selection that specifies whether the system checks the values:

T Examine for trend
S Examine for seasonal fluctuations
A Examine for trend and seasonal fluctuations


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Selection Procedure

This procedure defines how the system selects the optimum forecast model.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Ind. Param. Optimization

Indicator that causes the system to optimize the smoothing factors needed by the given forecast model.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Optimization Level

By determining the optimization level, you are specifying the increment with which the system is to carry out parameter optimization. The lower the increment, the more exact but also the more time consuming the optimization process will be.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Weighting Group

Key used with the "weighted moving average" forecast model to specify
•how many historical values are used to calculate the forecast and
•what weighting is given to each of the historical values


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Alpha Factor

The alpha factor is the smoothing factor for the basic value. The system uses this factor in the forecast to update the basic value.

Type: Number
Length: 3
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Beta Factor

The beta factor is the smoothing factor for the trend value. The system uses this factor to update the trend value in forecasting.

Type: Number
Length: 3
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Gamma Factor

The gamma factor is the smoothing factor for the seasonal index. The system uses this factor to update the seasonal index.

Type: Number
Length: 3
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Delta Factor

The delta factor is the smoothing factor for the mean absolute deviation (MAD). The system uses this factor to update the mean absolute deviation in forecasting.

Type: Number
Length: 3
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
   </Row>
  </Table>

    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Product Number*

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Plant*

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inspection Type*

Type: Text
Length: 30</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Preferred Inspection Type

If you set this indicator, the system creates preferred inspection lots with this inspection type for the corresponding inspection lot origins.
This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Active

If you set this indicator, inspection lots can be processed for this product and inspection type. This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Post to Inspection Stock

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Serial Numbers Possible

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Dynamic Modification Rule

Contains the definition of inspection stages and the conditions that lead to changes in inspection stages.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Skips Allowed

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.
If you set this indicator, skips are allowed for inspection characteristics during sample calculation.
If you do not set this indicator, the system chooses the next inspection stage in the dynamic modification rule that is not a skip, instead of the skip defined in the quality level during sample calculation.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inspection Lot Summary

This field is only relevant for inspections of warehouse-managed stock.
You can group goods that need to be inspected into one single inspection lot. For example, you can group delivered products by purchase order so that even if the products are delivered in multiple deliveries, the products are grouped into one inspection lot.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Control Lot Creation

Control of Inspection Lot Creation (Lot Summary)

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inspection with Task List

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.
If you set this indicator, the inspection is performed based on the task list

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inspect by Batch

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Automatic Specification Assignment

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.
If this indicator is set, the system trys to assign a task list or a material specification automatically.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inspect Characteristics

If you set this indicator, characteristic-based results recording is performed for the inspection lot.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Sampling Procedure

Sampling Procedure by which the sample size for an inspection is determined.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">100% Inspection

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.
If you set this indicator, the system treats the inspection lot size as the sample size.
Dependencies: If you define a 100% inspection for the product, you must manually valuate the inspection characteristics.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inspection Percentage

Inspection Percentage
This field is only relevant, when you carry out an inspection without reference to a task list or material specification. In this case, the total sample size is calculated on the basis of the percentage rate taken from the lot size.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Manual Sample Calculation

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.
If you set this indicator, you must trigger the sample calculation manually in the inspection lot.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Manual Sample Entry

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.
If you set this indicator, you must manually enter the sample size for the inspection lot.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Average Inspection Days

Average duration of an inspection (in days) for each inspection type.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Automatic Usage Decision

If you set this indicator, the system can automatically make usage decisions for inspection lots.
The inspection lots must meet the following conditions:
All characteristics have been completed.
None of the characteristics have been rejected.
No defects have been recorded, or quality notifications created.
The waiting time must have elapsed.


Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Quality Score Procedure

The procedure used to calculate the quality score for the inspection lot.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>

   <Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Product Number*

A key that uniquely identifies the product.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">MRP Area*

Number of the MRP area for which product requirements planning should be carried out separately.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Plant*

Key uniquely identifying a plant.
In Logistics a plant is an organizational unit for dividing an enterprise according to production, procurement, maintenance, and products planning.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">MRP Type

Key that determines whether and how the product is planned. This field becomes mandatory if MRP data should be migrated.
Depending on the MRP type other fields are becomming mandatory eg if you choose 'VB' for reorder-point planning you also have to specify the Reorder Point, MRP controller, Lot Sizing Procedure ...

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">MRP Controller

Specifies the number of the MRP controller or group of MRP controllers responsible for product planning for the product.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">MRP Group

The MRP group contains all the products from the point of view of MRP for assigning special control parameters for the total planning run. These control parameters include, for example, the strategy group, the consumption mode, and the planning horizon.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Reorder Point

For MRP Type 'VB' (Reorder-Point-Planning) you have to specify the reorder point for reorder planning. In this case this field becomes mandatory. If the stock falls below this quantity, the system flags the product for requirements planning.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planning Time Fence

The planning fence time becomes required if you are working with MRP type which includes a firming type. This is for example the case for MRP type P1-P4 (Forecast Consumption, Auto/Manual Firming).
The planning time fence specifies a period within which no automatic changes are to be made to the master plan.
The planning time fence is maintained in workdays.


Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planning Cycle

Key that determines the day on which the product is planned and ordered.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Lot Sizing Procedure

Key that determines which lot-sizing procedure the system uses within products planning to calculate the quantity to be procured or produced.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Minimum Lot Size

Minimum procurement quantity.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Maximum Lot Size

Quantity that is not allowed to be exceeded during procurement.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Fixed Lot Size

Please enter a value if you are working with Lot Sizing Procedure 'Fixed order quantity'. The fixed lot size is then a required field.
Note: In this case entries in fields: Minimum Lot Size, Maximum Lot Size and Rounding value will be reset.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Storage Cost Indicator

Indicator that specifies the storage costs percentage the system uses when calculating the lot size to determine storage costs.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Lot Size Independent Cost

Costs that are incurred, irrespective of lot size, for each purchase order or production order over and above the purchase order price or production costs.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Currency for Lot Size Ind. Cost

You must specify the currency for the Lot Size Independent Cost (currency of the company code belonging to the plant).

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Assembly Scrap (%)

Percentage scrap that occurs during production of the product if the product is an assembly.
The assembly scrap is used in products planning to calculate the lot size of the assembly. The system increases the quantity to be produced by the scrap quantity calculated.

Type: Number
Length: 5
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Maximum Stock Level

Quantity of the product in this plant that may not be exceeded.
In products planning, the maximum stock level is used only if you have chosen Replenish to maximum stock level as the lot-sizing procedure; that is, you have entered HB as the lot size key.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Rounding Value

Value to a multiple of which the system rounds up the procurement quantity.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Takt Time

If a requirement quantity (for example, for capacity reasons) cannot be procured in a single lot, you have to schedule several receipts. In conjunction with the overlap indicator in the lot size, you can use the takt time to specify that these receipts are offset, that is, that they are delayed by the takt time.
You enter the takt time in workdays.


Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Rounding Profile

Key that the system uses to adjust the order proposal quantity to deliverable units.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Safety Stock

Specifies the quantity whose purpose is to satisfy unexpectedly high demand in the coverage period.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Service Level Warehouse

Percentage specifying what proportion of the requirement is to be covered by the warehouse stock.

Type: Number
Length: 3
Decimal: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Coverage Profile

The range of coverage profile contains the parameters for calculating the dynamic safety stock. This is a statistical calculation on the basis of average daily requirements.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Safety Time Indicator

You use this indicator to switch on the safety time actual range of coverage for a product in MRP.
If you define a safety time, the requirements in MRP are brought forward on the time axis by the number of workdays you define here. The actual range of coverage corresponds to the number of days, by which the requirements are brought forward. Using this indicator you can activate the safety time and you can set whether all requirements or only independent requirements (sales order, planned independent requirements, and so on) are to be brought forward.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Safety Time (in Workdays)

In this field, you define the number of workdays for the safety time/actual range of coverage. If you define a safety time, the requirements in MRP are brought forward on the time axis by the number of workdays you define here.

Type: Number
Length: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Safety Time Period Profile

The period profile for the safety time / actual range of coverage contains the periods (stating to/from date) with the safety time/actual range of coverage that is valid for each period.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">MRP Relevancy for Dep. Requirements

MRP relevancy (Materials Requirements Planning) for dependent requirements:
This indicator controls whether dependent requirements are relevant to MRP or not. Dependent requirements include dependent reservations and stock transfer requirements. You only use this indicator in connection with planning strategies for make-to-stock production, assembly planning.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">MRP Safety Stock Method

The MRP Safety Stock Method provides different options to introduce a safety buffer.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Special Procurement Type

The special procurement type is used to precisely define how in-house production and external procurement is to be carried out. Example: Special Procurement for External Procurement can be Consignment, Subcontracting ...

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Default Storage Loc. for Ext. Proc.

Default storage location for external procurement.
Storage location that is proposed in the purchase requisition in products planning for subsequent storage of the product. In the case of a product procured externally, this storage location is proposed in the planned order in products planning.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planning Calendar

Three character number (numeric or using letters) that specifically identifies a PPS-planning calendar.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Consider Planned Delivery Time

This is an indicator field. If you use Planned Delivery Time of the MRP Area, enter X. If you use Planned Delivery Time of the Plant, leave the field empty.

Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planned Delivery Time

Number of calendar days needed to obtain the product or service if it is procured externally.

Type: Number
Length: 3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Issue Storage Location

Default storage location for produced inhouse.
In the case of a product produced in-house, this is the key of the storage location that is copied to the planned order, production order, or run schedule quantity. If the product is a component, it is the issuing storage location to which a backflush is posted.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>

   <Row ss:AutoFitHeight="0">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Product Number*

A key that uniquely identifies the product.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Valuation Area*

Valuation area is the organizational level at which the product is valuated.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Valuation Type

This is a further subdivision of the valuation category. The valuation category defines the valuation types allowed for a product.
If a product is valuated by origin (for example, valuation category H), you can define the possible countries of origin as valuation types.
For valuation category 'Single batch Valuation' you have to provide for each batch an own valuation type with the detailed price information.
Note: you have to define one valuation header record with specified valuation category and initial valuation type and one dependent record for each valuation type. Further information can be found in the migration object documentation under Mapping instructions - Single Batch Valuation and Split Valuation.

Type: Text
Length: 10</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Valuation Category

Determines whether stocks of the material are valuated together or separately.
In the case of split valuation, this indicator also determines which valuation types are allowed, that is, the criteria by which stocks can be valuated.
Further information can be found the migration object documentation under Mapping instructions - Single Batch Valuation and Split Valuation.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Price Control Determination

The Price determination indicator determines whether price determination is:
•Transaction-based
•Single-level / multilevel




Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Valuation Class*

Assignment of a product to a group of G/L accounts

With other factors, the valuation class determines the G/L accounts that are updated as a result of a valuation-relevant transaction or event such as a goods movement.
The valuation class makes it possible to:
•Post the stock values of products of the same product type to different G/L accounts
•Post the stock values of products of different product types to the same G/L account

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Valuation Class for Sales Order

Default value for the valuation class for valuated sales order stocks of the product.
You need specify a valuation class here only if you want to assign a different valuation class to this type of stock than that assigned to other valuated stocks of the product. This makes it possible to define other allowed G/L accounts for these stocks.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Valuation Class for Project Stock

Default value for the valuation class for valuated project stocks of the product.
You need specify a valuation class here only if you want to assign a different valuation class to this type of stock than that assigned to other valuated stocks of the product. This makes it possible to define other allowed G/L accounts for these stocks.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Price Control*

Indicates the price control used to valuate the stock of a product. You have the following options:
• S - Standard price
• V - Moving average price


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Currency*

You must specify the company code currency belonging to the valuation area.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inventory Price Moving Average

Moving average price if the product has price control indicator 'V' for moving average price.
The system calculates the moving average price automatically by dividing the product value in the stock account by the total of all storage location stocks in the plant concerned. It changes the price with each valuation-relevant movement.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inventory Price Standard Price

Standard price of the product if the product has price control indicator 'S' for standard price.
The valuation of product stocks at standard prices means that all goods movements are valuated at the same price over an extended period.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Price Unit

Number of units to which the price refers.

Type: Number
Length: 5</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Future Price

Price at which the product will be valuated as from a precise date in the future.
The future price is valid as of the date you enter in the relevant field.



Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Date of Which Future Price Is Valid From

Type: Date</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planned Price 1

Price that the system can take as a basis for product costing.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planned Price Date 1

Date as from which planned price 1 is valid for the product.

Type: Date</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planned Price 2

Price that the system can take as a basis for product costing.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planned Price Date 2

Date as from which planned price 2 is valid for the product.

Type: Date</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planned Price 3

Price that the system can take as a basis for product costing.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Planned Price Date 3

Date as from which planned price 3 is valid for the product.

Type: Date</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Tax Price 1

Price at which the product is valuated for tax purposes.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Tax Price 2

Price at which the product is valuated for tax purposes, and which is derived in the determination of lowest value. It relates to the price unit of the previous year.

Type: Number
Length: 13

Length: 80</Data></Cell>

A devaluation indicator representing the number of years a product has already been classed as "slow or non-moving".

Type: Number
Length: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Usage of the Product

Use for BRAZIL only !

This indicator shows the intended usage of a particular product in inventory. Please note that each usage of a product must have a separate valuation. As soon as a product has more than one usage in a valuation area then valuation types can be used.


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Origin of the Product

Use for BRAZIL only !
This indicator shows whether the products were produced inside Brazil or were imported. If the goods were imported, it also indicates whether they were imported directly by the company or not.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Produced In-House

Use for BRAZIL only !

This indicator shows whether the product was produced by the company or another one. It is used for purpose of CFOP determination.
If the indicator is set the product was produced by the company. If the indicator is not set the product was produced by another company.


Type: Text
Length: 1</Data></Cell>

This is an indicator field. If the criterion is met, enter X. If not, leave the field empty.

Length: 80</Data></Cell>

    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Valuation Area*

Valuation area is the organizational level at which the product is valuated.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Valuation Type

This is a further subdivision of the valuation category. The valuation category defines the valuation types allowed for a product.
If a product is valuated by origin (for example, valuation category H), you can define the possible countries of origin as valuation types.
For valuation category 'Single batch Valuation' you have to provide for each batch an own valuation type with the detailed price information.
Note: you have to define one valuation header record with specified valuation category and initial valuation type and one dependent record for each valuation type. Further information can be found in the migration object documentation under Mapping instructions - Single Batch Valuation and Split Valuation.

Type: Text
Length: 10</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Valuation Category

Determines whether stocks of the material are valuated together or separately.
In the case of split valuation, this indicator also determines which valuation types are allowed, that is, the criteria by which stocks can be valuated.
Further information can be found the migration object documentation under Mapping instructions - Single Batch Valuation and Split Valuation.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Currency Type*

The currency type specifies the role of a currency in the system. In addition to the local currency (company code currency), you can use parallel currencies per company code.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Price Control*

Indicates the price control used to valuate the stock of a product. You have the following options:
• S - Standard price
• V - Moving average price


Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Currency*

You must specify the currency belonging to the provided currency type.

Type: Text
Length: 80</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inventory Price Moving Average

Moving average price if the product has price control indicator 'V' for moving average price.
The system calculates the moving average price automatically by dividing the product value in the stock account by the total of all storage location stocks in the plant concerned. It changes the price with each valuation-relevant movement.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Inventory Price Standard Price

Standard price of the product if the product has price control indicator 'S' for standard price.
The valuation of product stocks at standard prices means that all goods movements are valuated at the same price over an extended period.

Type: Number
Length: 13
Decimal: 2</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s111"><Data ss:Type="String">Price Unit

Number of units to which the price refers.

Length: 5</Data></Cell>
